$$p(x) = \frac{x^4-3x^3+15x-25}{x^2-3x+5}.$$', "We can use polynomial long division or synthetic division to perform this division. Here's the polynomial long division:




\[
\begin{array}{c|ccccc}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{x^2} & -2x & +3 \\
\cline{2-6}
x^2-3x+5 & x^4 & -3x^3 & 0x^2 & +15x & -25 \\
\multicolumn{2}{r}{-x^4} & +3x^3 & -5x^2 \\
\cline{2-4}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{0} & 0x^3 & -5x^2 \\
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & +5x^2 & -15x & +25 \\
\cline{3-5}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & 0 & 0x & 0 \\
\end{array}
\]", 'Therefore, we have
$$p(x) = \frac{x^4-3x^3+15x-25}{x^2-3x+5} = x^2 - 2x + 3.$$']
